Oracle Maven Repository
=
Starting in 2016, Oracle started posting its drivers to a secure Oracle Maven repository, and they post the instructions for how to use the repository on [their site][2].  The process looks like this:

 1. [Register][3] for the site, if needed.
 2. Create a Maven Master password for encryption, if needed.
    ```bash
    mvn -emp [YOUR MASTER PASSWORD]
    ```
 3. Add the Oracle server to your Maven settings.xml (~/.m2/settings.xml).
    ```xml
    &lt;servers&gt;
      &lt;server&gt;
        &lt;id&gt;maven.oracle.com &lt;/id&gt;
        &lt;username&gt;YOUR ORACLE USERNAME&lt;/username&gt;
        &lt;password&gt;YOUR ORACLE PASSWORD&lt;/password&gt;
